Propping of Precast Wall Panels
Propping Precast Panels

Complete a visual inspection of the panel props for damage to props. Check for anything broken, bent, cracks in welds and elongation of shear pin holes. If the prop fails visual inspection ensure it is marked as NOT FOR USE and placed away from all other props and arrange return for inspection by supplier.
Install panel props as per the approved panel propping documents provided by the supplier. Take a photo of panel prop identification.
Ensure the Shear Pin (not a bolt or Reo) is connected to the outer and inner sections, secured with an R clip and free from defects.
Ensure the anchor bolts are as per the propping design and installed correctly.
